  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit (200 degrees Celsius).",
    "On a lightly floured surface, roll out puff pastry to a thickness of about 1/8 inch.",
    "Cut out circles of pastry using a cookie cutter or the rim of a glass.",
    "Place a tablespoon of shrimp mixture in the center of each pastry circle.",
    "Brush the edges of the pastry with egg wash.",
    "Fold the pastry in half over the filling and press the edges to seal.",
    "Use a fork to crimp the edges and create a decorative border.",
    "Place the empanadas on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.",
    "Brush the tops of the empanadas with olive oil and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.",
    "Bake for 20-25 minutes, or until the pastry is golden brown.",
    "Serve hot with a side of salsa or guacamole."
  ],
